==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Diagnostic
<hw>Di`ag*nos"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ able to
distinguish, fr. <?/: cf. F. <ets>diagnostique</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Pertaining to, or furnishing, a diagnosis; indicating the nature of
a disease.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Diagnostic</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Diagnostic
<hw>Di`ag*nos"tic</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The mark or symptom by which
one disease is known or distinguished from others.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Diagnosticate</ent>⟦br⟧
